1
00:00:13,472 --> 00:00:14,765
Next story.

2
00:00:15,474 --> 00:00:19,061
Breaking news on the Okutama
serial kidnapping and killing case.

3
00:00:19,937 --> 00:00:23,399
Police report
numerous eyewitness sightings.

4
00:00:23,482 --> 00:00:27,403
However, no concrete evidence
has surfaced so far.

5
00:00:27,486 --> 00:00:30,239
We had a special fortune reading performed

6
00:00:30,322 --> 00:00:33,033
by Shingetsu Nathan, the practitioner
of the Dragon-Surge Style divination.

7
00:00:33,117 --> 00:00:36,412
He has given his predictions
on the culprit.

8
00:00:36,495 --> 00:00:39,665
He predicts the killer
is a thin, handsome male in his late 30s

9
00:00:39,749 --> 00:00:42,793
with a hunched back. What do you think?

10
00:00:42,877 --> 00:00:46,672
Mr. Nathan has
successfully predicted events in the past.

11
00:00:47,214 --> 00:00:48,799
They're here.

12
00:00:48,883 --> 00:00:50,009
Coming.

13
00:00:50,092 --> 00:00:51,635
Do we have a guest?

14
00:00:51,719 --> 00:00:53,429
Miss Emma, please clear the table.

15
00:00:54,054 --> 00:00:55,222
Sure.

16
00:01:04,190 --> 00:01:05,357
Thank you.

17
00:01:07,777 --> 00:01:09,695
-For you.
-Thank you very much.

18
00:01:10,613 --> 00:01:11,739
Enjoy.

19
00:01:11,822 --> 00:01:12,865
Thank you.

20
00:01:15,785 --> 00:01:19,955
This is Diane. The architect
who designed this guest house.

21
00:01:20,623 --> 00:01:22,750
-It's wonderful to meet you.
-Nice to meet you.

22
00:01:22,833 --> 00:01:25,252
And… the salesperson.

23
00:01:25,336 --> 00:01:29,507
I'm Mathew. Shota Mathew.
Did you forget my name?

24
00:01:29,590 --> 00:01:34,053
I've been with Diane's architectural
studio since her father was in charge.

25
00:01:34,804 --> 00:01:36,972
They will lead the reconstruction
of the main house,

26
00:01:37,056 --> 00:01:38,849
so you'll see them around.

27
00:01:38,933 --> 00:01:40,017
Understood.

28
00:01:41,352 --> 00:01:45,397
This is Emma. She's boarding
with me for the time being for reasons.

29
00:01:45,481 --> 00:01:48,275
-I'm Sho Emma. It's a pleasure.
-Likewise.

30
00:01:48,359 --> 00:01:50,194
-Good to meet you.
-Good to meet you too.

31
00:01:52,905 --> 00:01:54,698
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

32
00:02:00,871 --> 00:02:04,792
How are your parents, Miss Chloe?

33
00:02:05,876 --> 00:02:07,419
I called to tell them about the fire.

34
00:02:07,503 --> 00:02:09,797
They gave me an earful,
saying I shouldn't be living alone,

35
00:02:09,880 --> 00:02:11,507
so I hung up right away.

36
00:02:12,091 --> 00:02:14,802
Your parents live elsewhere?

37
00:02:15,636 --> 00:02:17,054
Miss Chloe's parents

38
00:02:17,137 --> 00:02:20,516
live on an upper floor
of a city high-rise.

39
00:02:21,100 --> 00:02:23,227
A newly built apartment in the city center

40
00:02:23,310 --> 00:02:25,855
is more comfortable than
an old house where cold drafts seep in.

41
00:02:25,938 --> 00:02:29,024
A salesperson that leaks personal info
must be detrimental to your business.

42
00:02:29,108 --> 00:02:30,985
Yes. I'll terminate him.

43
00:02:31,068 --> 00:02:33,571
What? Oh, sorry.

44
00:02:33,654 --> 00:02:36,156
I thought there'd be no harm
since you two seem close.

45
00:02:38,158 --> 00:02:41,996
Switching gears.
I saw some signage by the entrance.

46
00:02:42,079 --> 00:02:44,707
Did you start a fortune-telling business?

47
00:02:44,790 --> 00:02:47,751
Yes. I'm only open once a week,
on Sundays.

48
00:02:47,835 --> 00:02:51,297
Remember when you gave me a reading,
and your predictions came true?

49
00:02:52,047 --> 00:02:55,050
Yes. When you were deciding
to go independent.

50
00:02:55,134 --> 00:02:57,469
-Yes.
-How nice.

51
00:02:57,553 --> 00:03:00,264
Miss Chloe, won't you read my fortune too?

52
00:03:00,806 --> 00:03:03,100
A salesperson who's overly friendly
with his clients…

53
00:03:03,183 --> 00:03:04,518
I'll terminate him.

54
00:03:05,227 --> 00:03:06,812
Where do you draw the line then?

55
00:03:06,896 --> 00:03:09,148
-Enjoy.
-Thank you.

56
00:03:09,231 --> 00:03:10,941
How considerate. Thank you.

57
00:03:12,610 --> 00:03:14,612
Back to business.

58
00:03:14,695 --> 00:03:18,073
Will this be a total remodeling?

59
00:03:19,366 --> 00:03:20,659
Well…

60
00:03:21,493 --> 00:03:23,996
The main house
didn't completely burn down.

61
00:03:24,955 --> 00:03:26,081
I see.

62
00:03:27,082 --> 00:03:28,459
As an architect,

63
00:03:28,542 --> 00:03:33,255
I'd like to make use of the main house's
eclectic revivalism features.

64
00:03:33,339 --> 00:03:36,508
Let's preserve those features
the best we can, and…

65
00:03:36,592 --> 00:03:40,721
I believe your father
is the original architect.

66
00:03:40,804 --> 00:03:45,476
Yes. This is the first house
he designed upon returning to Japan.

67
00:03:46,518 --> 00:03:50,898
This provincial-style house inspired
by French and Belgian architecture…

68
00:03:50,981 --> 00:03:52,816
I lost them there.

69
00:03:53,484 --> 00:03:56,195
Diane is rather particular
about her tastes, you see.

70
00:03:56,779 --> 00:04:01,742
She drives a compact car by a French
manufacturer. It's a convertible.

71
00:04:01,825 --> 00:04:03,619
Fancy, I know.

72
00:04:03,702 --> 00:04:05,663
I hear when she separated
from her ex-husband--

73
00:04:05,746 --> 00:04:06,872
Mathew?

74
00:04:08,916 --> 00:04:10,042
Was that taboo?

75
00:04:10,125 --> 00:04:15,339
Hold on, I was being mindful
to not discuss her personal life…

76
00:04:15,422 --> 00:04:19,551
First of all, don't talk
about somebody else's private life.

77
00:04:20,344 --> 00:04:23,180
Sorry. I was just trying
to make conversation…

78
00:04:24,014 --> 00:04:28,560
Speaking of someone who's particular,
you're very fashion-conscious.

79
00:04:29,186 --> 00:04:30,396
Am I?

80
00:04:30,896 --> 00:04:34,692
But don't you want to wear clothes
that put a pep in your step?

81
00:04:34,775 --> 00:04:37,319
I wear something that makes me happy
when I'm meeting people.

82
00:04:37,403 --> 00:04:39,822
But when I'm at home,
I want to be relaxed,

83
00:04:39,905 --> 00:04:41,907
so I tend to wear silk.

84
00:04:41,991 --> 00:04:44,660
That was silk you wore…

85
00:04:45,411 --> 00:04:48,288
You're picky when it comes
to fashion too, Emma.

86
00:04:48,372 --> 00:04:51,291
You wear neutrals for your basic fit,
then wear bright pajamas.

87
00:04:51,375 --> 00:04:52,459
Indeed.

88
00:04:52,543 --> 00:04:55,254
I cycle through ten simple items
in black, white, gray, or beige.

89
00:04:55,337 --> 00:04:57,798
That way, I can blend in anywhere.

90
00:04:58,716 --> 00:05:00,426
So you're like Steve Jobs.

91
00:05:00,509 --> 00:05:02,678
I don't think hers is quite like
Steve Jobs' stoicism.

92
00:05:02,761 --> 00:05:04,638
And she doesn't wear just one outfit.

93
00:05:05,764 --> 00:05:08,809
Since I've been on a job hunt recently,

94
00:05:08,892 --> 00:05:12,771
I'm trying to wear neutrals
that won't offend anyone.

95
00:05:15,024 --> 00:05:16,567
And now, I'm boarding rent-free.

96
00:05:17,151 --> 00:05:19,778
I don't have the luxury
of wearing the clothes I like.

97
00:05:21,113 --> 00:05:26,076
That's why, at least to sleep,
I wear cheery pink polka dots.

98
00:05:28,328 --> 00:05:31,373
I was merely stating facts.

99
00:05:31,457 --> 00:05:33,834
I never said
you shouldn't wear flashy clothes.

100
00:05:35,586 --> 00:05:37,296
They say what you wear to sleep

101
00:05:37,379 --> 00:05:40,924
reveals your actual taste in fashion.

102
00:05:41,008 --> 00:05:44,511
Speaking of,
I wear a silk pajama to sleep--

103
00:05:44,595 --> 00:05:49,058
-Sorry, shall we continue?
-Wait, I--

104
00:05:49,141 --> 00:05:51,727
-Hey, I was--
-Now, please take a look.

105
00:05:51,810 --> 00:05:54,063
-Let me see…
-Listen…

106
00:05:54,146 --> 00:05:55,647
I wear a silk pajama.

107
00:05:55,731 --> 00:05:57,399
This is the image of the finished house.

108
00:05:57,483 --> 00:06:00,486
Today, I wore this pink necktie, and…

109
00:06:00,569 --> 00:06:01,820
What about…

110
00:06:14,666 --> 00:06:16,210
-Chloe.
-Emma.

111
00:06:16,293 --> 00:06:17,836
-Chloe et Emma.
-Chloe et Emma.

112
00:06:23,383 --> 00:06:27,805
CHRONICLE CARD FORTUNE-TELLING
SORT

113
00:06:27,888 --> 00:06:29,765
RITSUKO BABA
SUGINAMI - APRIL 11TH, 2006

114
00:06:29,848 --> 00:06:31,058
Ritsuko Baba.

115
00:06:31,683 --> 00:06:32,684
Yes.

116
00:06:33,352 --> 00:06:36,146
So, what brings you in today?

117
00:06:37,564 --> 00:06:42,528
I think my boyfriend, who attends
the same university as me, is cheating.

118
00:06:43,362 --> 00:06:45,781
You think he's two-timing?

119
00:06:45,864 --> 00:06:47,783
Well, yes. For now.

120
00:06:48,617 --> 00:06:52,621
But I think he wants to get back together.

121
00:06:54,039 --> 00:06:55,249
Get back together?

122
00:06:55,791 --> 00:06:56,875
Yes.

123
00:06:57,793 --> 00:06:59,628
He might be cheating on me with his ex.

124
00:07:02,673 --> 00:07:06,927
Maybe he got tired of me
because I'm gloomy and don't stand out.

125
00:07:08,303 --> 00:07:11,598
Although, he's the one who insisted
I tone down my looks.

126
00:07:13,600 --> 00:07:14,601
What do you mean?

127
00:07:15,519 --> 00:07:19,022
He doesn't like it when I stand out.

128
00:07:20,357 --> 00:07:22,693
We started dating in high school.

129
00:07:22,776 --> 00:07:25,195
At first, he complimented
everything about me.

130
00:07:25,988 --> 00:07:29,533
But recently, he's either critical of
or disappointed in me.

131
00:07:31,493 --> 00:07:32,661
My parents

132
00:07:32,744 --> 00:07:36,623
always told me to be careful
because men go for girls like me.

133
00:07:37,833 --> 00:07:41,879
Maybe that's why my guard was
always up around men.

134
00:07:43,463 --> 00:07:46,758
He was the only one
who broke down my walls.

135
00:07:46,842 --> 00:07:48,468
I don't want to lose him.

136
00:07:52,222 --> 00:07:54,558
So you want to know

137
00:07:55,267 --> 00:07:58,228
what the future holds for you two?

138
00:07:59,479 --> 00:08:00,522
Yes.

139
00:08:01,523 --> 00:08:02,691
Understood.

140
00:08:31,053 --> 00:08:34,348
-Thank you. You're good to go.
-Okay.

141
00:08:44,983 --> 00:08:46,443
Hello.

142
00:08:46,526 --> 00:08:49,029
-Hello.
-Do you have a reservation?

143
00:08:49,112 --> 00:08:51,448
Yes. I'm Masahiko Sorita.

144
00:08:51,531 --> 00:08:53,283
Come have a seat.

145
00:08:59,665 --> 00:09:03,293
Please write down your name,
address and birthday.

146
00:09:03,377 --> 00:09:04,378
'Kay.

147
00:09:15,097 --> 00:09:17,140
MASAHIKO SORITA
SHINJUKU - JUNE 28TH, 2002

148
00:09:17,224 --> 00:09:20,435
Masahiko Sorita. Are you employed?

149
00:09:21,561 --> 00:09:22,729
Yes.

150
00:09:23,355 --> 00:09:24,731
So…

151
00:09:24,815 --> 00:09:27,401
I like someone,
but I can't get her to trust me.

152
00:09:28,193 --> 00:09:29,778
I don't know how to move forward.

153
00:09:30,612 --> 00:09:31,738
Okay.

154
00:09:32,322 --> 00:09:35,534
She works at a café near my work.

155
00:09:36,952 --> 00:09:40,372
I try to approach her,
but she brushes me off.

156
00:09:40,956 --> 00:09:43,250
Do you make it sound like a joke?

157
00:09:43,333 --> 00:09:46,878
Not at all.
She must know how serious I am.

158
00:09:48,005 --> 00:09:52,342
Well, I'm signed with a modeling agency.
I'm a model.

159
00:09:54,011 --> 00:09:55,971
This girl I'm interested in is…

160
00:09:56,555 --> 00:10:00,934
Well, she's not conventionally
beautiful or attractive.

161
00:10:03,020 --> 00:10:05,856
That must be why she doesn't believe me.

162
00:10:05,939 --> 00:10:09,818
As in, she doesn't think
she measures up to you?

163
00:10:10,902 --> 00:10:12,029
Probably.

164
00:10:13,488 --> 00:10:18,327
Well, I'm not good with the popular type.

165
00:10:19,077 --> 00:10:21,997
I find them intimidating,
so I understand where she's coming from.

166
00:10:23,206 --> 00:10:26,376
But I feel at ease
when I'm around girls like her.

167
00:10:27,461 --> 00:10:29,087
I don't have to pretend I'm someone else.

168
00:10:29,713 --> 00:10:33,508
I want her to know the real me,
not just my looks, and then trust me.

169
00:10:36,595 --> 00:10:39,348
What if you told her that, word for word?

170
00:10:40,432 --> 00:10:43,560
I mean… I already have.

171
00:10:45,604 --> 00:10:46,730
I see.

172
00:10:47,397 --> 00:10:50,400
Then you want to know
how you can earn her trust.

173
00:10:50,901 --> 00:10:53,779
I will also read
what the future holds for you two.

174
00:10:54,863 --> 00:10:56,156
Please.

175
00:11:03,747 --> 00:11:06,625
First a pretty girl, then a handsome guy.

176
00:11:07,709 --> 00:11:10,712
Who would've known
your business would be such a hit?

177
00:11:10,796 --> 00:11:14,633
Maybe your business is a hot topic
in the Beautifuls' social circle.

178
00:11:15,509 --> 00:11:17,344
What kind of social circle is that?

179
00:11:18,720 --> 00:11:22,766
I guess… being attractive doesn't
stop you from having issues.

180
00:11:23,642 --> 00:11:25,811
Everyone's got issues.

181
00:11:26,395 --> 00:11:27,479
But…

182
00:11:28,313 --> 00:11:31,233
their cards for the near future
were the same.

183
00:11:31,316 --> 00:11:33,068
That took me by surprise.

184
00:11:33,652 --> 00:11:35,320
Which card was it?

185
00:11:36,154 --> 00:11:38,490
Thursday, reversed.

186
00:11:39,199 --> 00:11:41,076
Card of Greed.

187
00:11:41,785 --> 00:11:43,537
When this card is in reverse
when reading the future,

188
00:11:43,620 --> 00:11:45,914
it usually indicates
tumultuous relationships.

189
00:11:54,381 --> 00:11:55,715
Tumultuous?

190
00:11:59,553 --> 00:12:03,390
TRADITIONAL CAFÉ PARIS

191
00:12:04,224 --> 00:12:08,145
You can be attractive and still
have rough patches in relationships.

192
00:12:09,604 --> 00:12:11,273
What's the matter, Emma?

193
00:12:12,524 --> 00:12:13,733
You havin' romantic troubles?

194
00:12:14,359 --> 00:12:16,653
Want us retirees to lend an ear?

195
00:12:16,736 --> 00:12:17,821
We're here for ya.

196
00:12:17,904 --> 00:12:19,781
I was making a general statement.

197
00:12:19,865 --> 00:12:20,866
Know what?

198
00:12:20,949 --> 00:12:24,995
Attractive people tend to have
more issues in relationships.

199
00:12:25,078 --> 00:12:27,622
They get hit on more, you see.

200
00:12:27,706 --> 00:12:30,834
True. Now that you mention it, yes.

201
00:12:30,917 --> 00:12:32,669
That's right.

202
00:12:32,752 --> 00:12:34,921
Just like us.

203
00:12:36,965 --> 00:12:38,717
-Of course.
-Right?

204
00:12:38,800 --> 00:12:43,263
Back in our prime,
we broke a lot of girls' hearts.

205
00:12:43,847 --> 00:12:47,350
Because we wore tacky outfits to dates!

206
00:12:52,689 --> 00:12:53,899
Remember?

207
00:12:53,982 --> 00:12:55,984
You had a killer pick-up line.

208
00:12:56,735 --> 00:12:58,111
-Oh, that?
-Tell 'er.

209
00:13:00,238 --> 00:13:01,907
Go out with me,

210
00:13:02,782 --> 00:13:05,994
and I promise a lifetime of happiness…

211
00:13:08,371 --> 00:13:09,539
-For myself.
-For myself.

212
00:13:14,503 --> 00:13:16,004
This one was funnier.

213
00:13:16,087 --> 00:13:18,298
C'mon, don't be harsh.

214
00:13:18,924 --> 00:13:21,259
She liked this one more.

215
00:13:23,094 --> 00:13:25,055
-Thanks for the food.
-Till next time.

216
00:13:25,138 --> 00:13:26,389
Thank you for your patronage.

217
00:13:26,473 --> 00:13:27,974
Thank you.

218
00:13:28,058 --> 00:13:29,643
-Phew, it's hot!
-Sure is hot out.

219
00:13:39,986 --> 00:13:43,323
Your glasses hide it,

220
00:13:43,406 --> 00:13:46,660
but you're one of the Beautifuls,
just like Chloe.

221
00:13:47,786 --> 00:13:49,037
Beautifuls?

222
00:13:52,457 --> 00:13:55,961
Chloe took care of me
when I got caught between two girls.

223
00:13:56,044 --> 00:13:58,088
In a way, she saved me.

224
00:13:58,171 --> 00:13:59,256
Really?

225
00:14:00,382 --> 00:14:04,761
During my first year at a company,
two female coworkers

226
00:14:04,844 --> 00:14:07,305
started some huge drama fighting over me.

227
00:14:07,389 --> 00:14:09,849
It got so bad, I had to resign.

228
00:14:10,433 --> 00:14:11,851
Oh, dear.

229
00:14:11,935 --> 00:14:15,313
After that, I worked part-time
in the kitchen of a diner.

230
00:14:15,397 --> 00:14:18,149
But a similar thing happened.
A server and a kitchen worker

231
00:14:18,233 --> 00:14:20,610
fought over me in front of the customers.

232
00:14:21,194 --> 00:14:23,613
Good grief. You sure are popular.

233
00:14:24,364 --> 00:14:27,576
What's this? Why're you out here, Emi?

234
00:14:27,659 --> 00:14:30,078
The kitchen's slow.
I figured I'll help out.

235
00:14:30,829 --> 00:14:32,497
You sure that's the only reason?

236
00:14:33,164 --> 00:14:35,625
What're you insinuating?

237
00:14:35,709 --> 00:14:39,713
Nothing. Just thought you were trying
to show off to a special someone.

238
00:14:40,380 --> 00:14:42,591
Pipe down, you two.

239
00:14:42,674 --> 00:14:43,800
Mana, here's the parfait.

240
00:14:43,883 --> 00:14:47,220
I already went shopping
with Simon, you know.

241
00:14:47,304 --> 00:14:48,513
Shopping?

242
00:14:48,597 --> 00:14:51,641
You mean your breaks overlapped
so you took a quick shopping trip.

243
00:14:52,559 --> 00:14:54,394
Did I nail it?

244
00:14:54,477 --> 00:14:56,855
Sorry to drag you into this, Simon.

245
00:14:56,938 --> 00:15:01,443
Never mind me,
but there are customers around.

246
00:15:01,526 --> 00:15:04,362
Hear that?
You've put Simon in an awkward position.

247
00:15:04,446 --> 00:15:06,656
Simon is mine.

248
00:15:11,661 --> 00:15:13,371
I apologize for the trouble earlier.

249
00:15:14,456 --> 00:15:15,915
Sorry to bother you.

250
00:15:19,377 --> 00:15:21,212
Even though this place is part of a chain,

251
00:15:21,296 --> 00:15:24,799
you guys serve the best parfaits,
and that's why I come.

252
00:15:27,844 --> 00:15:29,638
And the customer from that day

253
00:15:29,721 --> 00:15:31,181
was Chloe.

254
00:15:34,643 --> 00:15:37,187
Right. Even though it was just a diner,

255
00:15:38,021 --> 00:15:41,024
she noticed the care I poured
into making parfaits.

256
00:15:42,150 --> 00:15:43,318
It made me happy.

257
00:15:45,362 --> 00:15:47,906
My shift was wrapping up,

258
00:15:47,989 --> 00:15:50,325
so I went after her and thanked her.

259
00:15:51,034 --> 00:15:54,371
We were talking when
my parfait-making hobby got brought up.

260
00:15:54,871 --> 00:15:56,956
I told her it was difficult

261
00:15:57,040 --> 00:16:00,960
to create an original parfait
at a diner chain.

262
00:16:01,044 --> 00:16:02,212
That's when…

263
00:16:03,713 --> 00:16:04,881
That's when?

264
00:16:06,007 --> 00:16:08,426
She asked me to tag along.

265
00:16:09,135 --> 00:16:11,721
She took me to a certain place.

266
00:16:17,936 --> 00:16:19,145
Where are we?

267
00:16:21,272 --> 00:16:22,899
Your dream of making parfaits…

268
00:16:23,858 --> 00:16:25,568
Ready to make it come true?

269
00:16:29,322 --> 00:16:33,159
TRADITIONAL CAFÉ PARIS

270
00:16:33,243 --> 00:16:34,953
"Your dream of making parfaits…"

271
00:16:35,036 --> 00:16:36,996
It's got a nice ring to it.

272
00:16:37,789 --> 00:16:40,125
She let me use the kitchen here.

273
00:16:40,208 --> 00:16:42,210
That's when I made
my first off-menu parfait.

274
00:16:42,293 --> 00:16:45,171
My first attempt at
the chocolate banana crunch parfait.

275
00:16:46,339 --> 00:16:48,508
So there's history to that parfait.

276
00:16:49,801 --> 00:16:51,553
In the end, I left the diner.

277
00:16:51,636 --> 00:16:56,099
I said I wanted to open a parfait shop
for grown-ups as I worked here.

278
00:16:56,891 --> 00:17:00,437
But the prior owner suddenly retired
due to his old age.

279
00:17:01,146 --> 00:17:04,315
That's how I ended up taking over.

280
00:17:04,399 --> 00:17:06,651
So that's the story.

281
00:17:06,735 --> 00:17:07,902
Yes.

282
00:17:09,988 --> 00:17:12,866
But the biggest relief

283
00:17:12,949 --> 00:17:15,869
is that Chloe doesn't try to date me,

284
00:17:15,952 --> 00:17:19,038
and she put me in a place
where I'm free from unwanted advances.

285
00:17:20,665 --> 00:17:22,625
I don't have to worry
about getting hit on.

286
00:17:23,126 --> 00:17:25,420
There's safety that comes with it.

287
00:17:27,005 --> 00:17:29,883
Also, I get to make parfaits every week.

288
00:17:31,217 --> 00:17:33,261
That's the story behind
the weekly parfait night.

289
00:17:33,344 --> 00:17:34,345
That's right.

290
00:17:35,013 --> 00:17:37,766
I don't mean to complain
after all she's done for me,

291
00:17:37,849 --> 00:17:39,559
but isn't she a bit too generous?

292
00:17:41,811 --> 00:17:46,107
But she hates it when people
come begging for her help.

293
00:17:46,191 --> 00:17:47,901
She can be quite cold to them.

294
00:17:47,984 --> 00:17:49,110
Really?

295
00:17:50,612 --> 00:17:55,074
She can't help but lend a hand
to people who've been wronged

296
00:17:55,950 --> 00:17:58,286
but are trying to better their situation.

297
00:17:58,369 --> 00:17:59,662
She's good-natured.

298
00:18:02,415 --> 00:18:08,046
So if I had said "please help me"
rather than "I hate to impose,"

299
00:18:08,129 --> 00:18:10,340
then maybe she wouldn't have
let me use her restroom.

300
00:18:10,965 --> 00:18:12,342
I've gotta be careful.

301
00:18:13,176 --> 00:18:16,012
She's letting me stay
out of sheer generosity.

302
00:18:16,095 --> 00:18:19,599
She might decide to kick me out
on a whim one day.

303
00:18:20,391 --> 00:18:23,394
Guess nothing's changed
since I lived with my ex.

304
00:18:26,981 --> 00:18:31,069
Speaking of, you said your relationship
wasn't on equal ground.

305
00:18:32,737 --> 00:18:34,280
When there's a power imbalance,

306
00:18:34,364 --> 00:18:37,992
I have to be careful I don't come across
as annoying or unlikable.

307
00:18:38,076 --> 00:18:41,079
Still, you have to be assertive to get by.

308
00:18:41,162 --> 00:18:44,666
When a tiny woman like me is quiet,
I get bulldozed over.

309
00:18:45,625 --> 00:18:47,001
I see.

310
00:18:47,585 --> 00:18:52,090
Be bold and carefully read people so that
I don't cross the line and be hated.

311
00:18:52,173 --> 00:18:54,008
That's my pro tip for life.

312
00:18:55,218 --> 00:18:57,720
That's quite challenging.

313
00:19:03,351 --> 00:19:05,436
-Welcome in.
-Welcome in.

314
00:19:06,938 --> 00:19:08,231
HARUKA MIMASAKA
MITAKA - MAY 3RD, 2005

315
00:19:08,314 --> 00:19:09,858
Haruka Mimasaka.

316
00:19:11,276 --> 00:19:12,569
Are you a student?

317
00:19:12,652 --> 00:19:15,572
Yes. I attend a university.

318
00:19:15,655 --> 00:19:18,783
What brings you in today?

319
00:19:19,450 --> 00:19:22,120
I'm getting approached by two men at once:

320
00:19:22,954 --> 00:19:27,417
my ex and a customer at work.

321
00:19:29,002 --> 00:19:32,463
Are you seeking guidance
on which man to date?

322
00:19:36,551 --> 00:19:38,803
Neither of them feel quite right.

323
00:19:39,846 --> 00:19:40,847
Meaning?

324
00:19:42,599 --> 00:19:46,269
My ex is my junior from middle school.

325
00:19:48,146 --> 00:19:50,189
Though he's younger,
he can be quite persistent.

326
00:19:50,273 --> 00:19:52,525
I gave in, and we dated for a while.

327
00:19:54,360 --> 00:19:56,237
Over time, he grew careless with me.

328
00:19:58,823 --> 00:20:01,492
Although he's not that attractive himself,

329
00:20:01,576 --> 00:20:03,328
he'd call me ugly and fat.

330
00:20:03,828 --> 00:20:06,497
Like, I'm well aware.
He didn't need to say those things.

331
00:20:08,750 --> 00:20:10,126
Even after we split,

332
00:20:10,209 --> 00:20:12,545
I still felt hurt by his words.

333
00:20:15,548 --> 00:20:16,633
I see.

334
00:20:18,718 --> 00:20:19,844
As for the other guy…

335
00:20:20,595 --> 00:20:24,057
I work at a café. The second floor
is a modeling agency.

336
00:20:24,849 --> 00:20:28,061
We have a lot of models that stop by.

337
00:20:30,563 --> 00:20:33,149
For some reason,

338
00:20:34,233 --> 00:20:36,527
one of the models
has taken an interest in me.

339
00:20:37,862 --> 00:20:40,490
But my ex says

340
00:20:41,074 --> 00:20:43,159
there's no way a hot guy would like me.

341
00:20:43,242 --> 00:20:45,453
That he must have some ulterior motives.

342
00:20:47,080 --> 00:20:50,500
Do you still talk to your ex?

343
00:20:51,542 --> 00:20:55,254
He… started messaging me a while ago.

344
00:20:56,297 --> 00:20:59,467
He irritates me,
so I've been ignoring him.

345
00:21:03,054 --> 00:21:04,347
Then…

346
00:21:05,264 --> 00:21:08,893
Do you want to know whether
this model is really in love with you?

347
00:21:14,649 --> 00:21:15,733
Well…

348
00:21:17,735 --> 00:21:19,070
How about this?

349
00:21:20,571 --> 00:21:24,659
Shall we ask the cards
what's making you feel unsettled?

350
00:21:26,577 --> 00:21:27,996
Yes, please.

351
00:21:29,580 --> 00:21:30,707
Understood.

352
00:22:06,367 --> 00:22:08,619
Oh,
mon…

353
00:22:10,079 --> 00:22:11,247
Dieu
!

354
00:22:40,651 --> 00:22:43,029
The first card.

355
00:22:43,988 --> 00:22:45,865
It represents your current situation.

356
00:22:47,784 --> 00:22:51,287
Friday, reversed. Card of Order.

357
00:22:52,914 --> 00:22:55,833
Things have been strange for you lately.

358
00:22:56,459 --> 00:22:59,128
Embarrassment. Turn of events.

359
00:23:00,546 --> 00:23:02,548
Do you feel uneasy

360
00:23:03,174 --> 00:23:06,135
about the turn of events so far
and out of balance because of it?

361
00:23:09,472 --> 00:23:10,556
Yes.

362
00:23:11,933 --> 00:23:15,520
Something about this model
feels off to me.

363
00:23:17,230 --> 00:23:20,733
He says he feels comfortable
around me because I'm not beautiful.

364
00:23:21,567 --> 00:23:24,612
It feels like he's hung up on appearance.

365
00:23:25,905 --> 00:23:26,948
I see.

366
00:23:28,950 --> 00:23:29,951
The second card.

367
00:23:31,119 --> 00:23:34,372
It represents something from the past
that continues to affect you.

368
00:23:36,332 --> 00:23:39,710
Saturday, reversed. Card of Stagnation.

369
00:23:39,794 --> 00:23:43,631
You feel stagnant because of
changes in how someone treats you.

370
00:23:44,382 --> 00:23:47,260
Something impedes your growth.

371
00:23:50,221 --> 00:23:53,307
The third card. The inner self.

372
00:23:53,933 --> 00:23:55,726
September, upright.

373
00:23:55,810 --> 00:23:57,228
Card of Reflection.

374
00:23:58,437 --> 00:23:59,480
Face…

375
00:23:59,981 --> 00:24:02,817
You've been reflecting on your appearance.

376
00:24:04,819 --> 00:24:07,572
But it's upright,

377
00:24:07,655 --> 00:24:09,740
meaning it's a change for the better.

378
00:24:11,284 --> 00:24:14,579
People may call me fat or ugly,

379
00:24:14,662 --> 00:24:16,914
but I don't let that stop me
from enjoying my life.

380
00:24:18,499 --> 00:24:21,544
People who judge others like that

381
00:24:21,627 --> 00:24:24,213
only do so
because they want to feel superior.

382
00:24:25,882 --> 00:24:28,551
The fourth card. The outer world.

383
00:24:29,677 --> 00:24:33,264
Monday, reversed. Card of Hesitation.

384
00:24:34,557 --> 00:24:36,309
A love triangle gone awry.

385
00:24:36,934 --> 00:24:40,229
Also, I sense a dark secret.

386
00:24:44,901 --> 00:24:46,152
The final card.

387
00:24:47,278 --> 00:24:50,615
It represents an event in the near future.

388
00:24:59,540 --> 00:25:00,583
What is it?

389
00:25:03,711 --> 00:25:05,546
Thursday, reversed.

390
00:25:06,422 --> 00:25:07,673
Card of Greed.

391
00:25:09,634 --> 00:25:10,885
You will

392
00:25:11,636 --> 00:25:14,180
be in a direct confrontation.

393
00:25:15,348 --> 00:25:18,351
You might get caught in a fray.

394
00:25:18,434 --> 00:25:19,644
What?

395
00:25:22,647 --> 00:25:24,941
Your lucky color is black.

396
00:25:25,942 --> 00:25:27,860
Black?

397
00:25:29,445 --> 00:25:31,197
Those earrings are black.

398
00:25:31,822 --> 00:25:33,407
Is it a slice of bread?

399
00:25:35,451 --> 00:25:38,412
Actually,

400
00:25:38,496 --> 00:25:43,125
my ex made this for me when we went
to an accessory-making workshop on a date.

401
00:25:44,168 --> 00:25:46,003
He made me burnt toast earrings.

402
00:25:47,797 --> 00:25:50,007
Crazy, huh? He made me burnt toast.

403
00:25:50,841 --> 00:25:53,970
I like that cheesy sense of humor.

404
00:25:55,263 --> 00:25:58,015
I thought about throwing them away
when we broke up,

405
00:25:58,808 --> 00:26:01,644
but they go with a lot of outfits,
and I just really like them.

406
00:26:02,478 --> 00:26:04,230
Those earrings didn't wrong you.

407
00:26:05,690 --> 00:26:09,193
Let go of relationships,
but not their keepsakes.

408
00:26:24,333 --> 00:26:26,294
This is it. I've pieced it together.

409
00:26:27,336 --> 00:26:29,505
Card of Greed completes the picture.

410
00:26:30,339 --> 00:26:31,465
What picture?

411
00:26:32,300 --> 00:26:34,969
The pretty girl, the model guy,
today's client

412
00:26:35,052 --> 00:26:39,974
and the shitty ex
just might form a love square.

413
00:26:40,057 --> 00:26:43,060
A "love square"? And who's the shitty ex?

414
00:26:43,769 --> 00:26:44,937
I'll explain.

415
00:26:47,982 --> 00:26:51,902
Ritsuko Baba, the first client,
is dating the shitty, abusive boyfriend.

416
00:26:51,986 --> 00:26:55,573
He used to date
Haruka Mimasaka, today's client.

417
00:26:55,656 --> 00:26:59,160
Masahiko Sorita, the model, likes her.

418
00:26:59,243 --> 00:27:02,872
See how everything lines up nicely?

419
00:27:02,955 --> 00:27:05,624
Can such a small community actually exist?

420
00:27:05,708 --> 00:27:09,545
Remember, I recently opened
this small fortune-telling business.

421
00:27:09,628 --> 00:27:12,048
I don't have a website,
social media page, or run newsletters.

422
00:27:12,131 --> 00:27:14,550
Not may people should know about me.

423
00:27:14,633 --> 00:27:18,387
At first, these things spread
through word of mouth.

424
00:27:18,471 --> 00:27:20,806
It's highly likely
they're connected somehow.

425
00:27:21,640 --> 00:27:22,892
I guess.

426
00:27:22,975 --> 00:27:26,479
To top it off, their last cards
for their future were Greed, reversed.

427
00:27:26,562 --> 00:27:28,189
This cannot be a coincidence.

428
00:27:28,272 --> 00:27:31,275
Everyone got the card
of relationship woes, huh?

429
00:27:31,359 --> 00:27:36,906
The shitty ex's identity was the last
piece I needed to complete the puzzle.

430
00:27:39,742 --> 00:27:43,996
And I found him
through my brilliant social media search.

431
00:27:44,705 --> 00:27:47,958
You shouldn't meddle
in your clients' personal lives.

432
00:27:48,042 --> 00:27:50,461
But I can't leave a mystery unresolved.

433
00:27:50,544 --> 00:27:53,798
You're just rubbernecking at this point.

434
00:27:54,298 --> 00:27:55,508
Look.

435
00:27:56,384 --> 00:27:59,512
Ken Tsukumo. First-year
economics major at Sawa University.

436
00:27:59,595 --> 00:28:01,806
He's the shitty ex.

437
00:28:01,889 --> 00:28:03,724
How'd you even find him?

438
00:28:04,308 --> 00:28:08,604
I found a mutual friend
of the pretty girl and the shitty ex

439
00:28:08,687 --> 00:28:12,525
who can't help but shares his entire life
online for all to see.

440
00:28:12,608 --> 00:28:14,110
THIS ACCOUNT IS PRIVATE

441
00:28:14,193 --> 00:28:15,611
Good golly.

442
00:28:15,694 --> 00:28:18,280
Ristuko Baba
is the prettiest girl in her grade.

443
00:28:18,364 --> 00:28:21,659
When she started dating Tsukumo,
people at their school were bewildered.

444
00:28:21,742 --> 00:28:23,160
It caused quite a commotion.

445
00:28:24,203 --> 00:28:27,581
I've heard of pretty girls
who date losers.

446
00:28:27,665 --> 00:28:31,669
No man is brave enough to ask out
a girl who's out of his league,

447
00:28:31,752 --> 00:28:35,714
except for an oblivious rando
who rushes in and dates her disastrously.

448
00:28:38,217 --> 00:28:41,387
I was also able to identify
Masahiko Sorita's modeling agency.

449
00:28:41,971 --> 00:28:46,058
Haruka Mimasaka's café is
directly below this agency's office.

450
00:28:46,142 --> 00:28:50,396
Tsukumo and Mimasaka were in the same
swim team at the same middle school.

451
00:28:50,479 --> 00:28:51,939
See how all the dots connect?

452
00:28:52,648 --> 00:28:57,820
Also, this must be the accessory workshop
they visited together.

453
00:28:57,903 --> 00:29:00,281
SAIBU WORKSHOP
CREATE A ONE-OF-A-KIND TREASURE

454
00:29:02,158 --> 00:29:05,286
Congratulation, Chloe.
You're a fully-fledged online stalker.

455
00:29:05,369 --> 00:29:07,121
Let me summarize.

456
00:29:07,204 --> 00:29:12,084
Although he has a girlfriend, the shitty
abusive boyfriend hits on his ex.

457
00:29:12,168 --> 00:29:14,795
His girlfriend catches on
that he's fooling around.

458
00:29:14,879 --> 00:29:17,047
The hot model
is into average-looking girls.

459
00:29:17,131 --> 00:29:22,928
The ex-girlfriend is wary
of both her ex and the model.

460
00:29:23,012 --> 00:29:25,764
Baba should break up
with a loser like him.

461
00:29:26,432 --> 00:29:28,476
That's what's scary about abusers.

462
00:29:28,559 --> 00:29:31,353
They manipulate their victims
by tearing down their confidence.

463
00:29:32,438 --> 00:29:34,398
So, what's your plan?

464
00:29:38,777 --> 00:29:45,409
Who am I, a complete stranger,
to meddle in their love affairs?

465
00:29:46,327 --> 00:29:49,788
You're merely sating your curiosity.
Thank goodness.

466
00:29:50,789 --> 00:29:51,957
Although…

467
00:29:52,917 --> 00:29:54,043
"Although"?

468
00:29:54,835 --> 00:29:57,338
I wonder what chaos would ensue

469
00:29:57,421 --> 00:30:00,007
should these four be put in the same room?

470
00:30:01,008 --> 00:30:02,468
Chloe?

471
00:30:02,551 --> 00:30:04,678
I'll set up bait.

472
00:30:04,762 --> 00:30:08,849
They might remember my face,
so I'll have you do the leg work, Emma.

473
00:30:08,933 --> 00:30:11,393
Don't drag me into it.

474
00:30:11,977 --> 00:30:14,021
Please, Steve Jobs.

475
00:30:14,104 --> 00:30:15,898
Now is the time

476
00:30:15,981 --> 00:30:19,068
to use your talent for blending in.

477
00:30:19,151 --> 00:30:21,362
Are you mocking me? Are you?

478
00:30:21,445 --> 00:30:22,655
Please, Steve!

479
00:30:23,280 --> 00:30:24,740
Are you ready?

480
00:30:25,616 --> 00:30:27,159
No!

481
00:30:29,203 --> 00:30:30,871
The first step…

482
00:30:37,920 --> 00:30:41,882
First, I make contact with Tsukumo
at his college campus

483
00:30:42,466 --> 00:30:45,886
by dropping the burnt-toast earring
and making it look like an accident.

484
00:30:45,970 --> 00:30:47,179
He then picks it up.

485
00:30:49,139 --> 00:30:50,140
Excuse me.

486
00:30:51,475 --> 00:30:52,518
That's mine.

487
00:30:53,310 --> 00:30:54,395
Here you go.

488
00:30:57,731 --> 00:31:01,151
Where did you get that earring?

489
00:31:01,819 --> 00:31:03,946
Isn't it cute?

490
00:31:04,029 --> 00:31:05,906
It's in the shape of burnt toast.

491
00:31:07,324 --> 00:31:11,495
I saw a café employee with it.
I thought it was cute, so I made one too.

492
00:31:12,288 --> 00:31:14,123
The employee said hers are also handmade.

493
00:31:14,206 --> 00:31:16,417
She said she cherishes them.

494
00:31:16,500 --> 00:31:21,255
I tell him I saw a café employee
with an identical set.

495
00:31:21,338 --> 00:31:24,008
By the way, what's the name of the café?

496
00:31:24,925 --> 00:31:27,761
Café Isnikyac.

497
00:31:28,345 --> 00:31:31,181
A modeling agency
set up office right above them,

498
00:31:31,265 --> 00:31:33,851
so they get a lot of attractive guys
who swing by.

499
00:31:34,643 --> 00:31:36,937
Well, not like that's any of your concern.

500
00:31:37,021 --> 00:31:38,022
Bye then.

501
00:31:38,105 --> 00:31:41,275
I feed him information
about Mimasaka's job.

502
00:31:41,900 --> 00:31:46,655
Mentioning the attractive customers
is part of my plan to make him jealous.

503
00:31:49,325 --> 00:31:52,161
While I'm on the move,

504
00:31:52,244 --> 00:31:55,998
I want you to chat with Mimasaka
about egg sandwiches.

505
00:31:56,915 --> 00:32:01,003
Nudge her so that she becomes
interested in Traditional Café Paris.

506
00:32:01,587 --> 00:32:02,880
FOLLOW

507
00:32:02,963 --> 00:32:05,090
Apparently, Mimasaka loves egg sandwiches.

508
00:32:05,174 --> 00:32:06,300
Excuse me.

509
00:32:06,383 --> 00:32:08,052
It should go according to plan.

510
00:32:08,135 --> 00:32:09,511
Thank you.

511
00:32:11,889 --> 00:32:14,099
Wow, this is delicious.

512
00:32:14,183 --> 00:32:17,269
Do you like egg sandwiches?
They're my favorites too.

513
00:32:18,437 --> 00:32:20,439
Are there any restaurants
or cafés around here

514
00:32:20,522 --> 00:32:24,151
that are known for their egg sandwiches?

515
00:32:25,986 --> 00:32:30,240
To name a few must-visit spots,
there are Café Trumbo and Jelly…

516
00:32:31,241 --> 00:32:32,743
But they're always packed.

517
00:32:32,826 --> 00:32:34,662
I know, right?

518
00:32:34,745 --> 00:32:38,332
That's why I go
to Traditional Café Paris in Mitaka.

519
00:32:38,415 --> 00:32:40,084
They're usually pretty empty
in the evening.

520
00:32:40,167 --> 00:32:42,670
Their egg sandwiches are exquisite.

521
00:32:42,753 --> 00:32:44,838
I see. Traditional Café…

522
00:32:45,798 --> 00:32:47,216
Paris.

523
00:32:47,299 --> 00:32:48,592
-Paris.
-Yup.

524
00:32:51,220 --> 00:32:52,638
Welcome in.

525
00:32:52,721 --> 00:32:53,722
Welcome in.

526
00:32:53,806 --> 00:32:55,057
I finally found you.

527
00:32:56,308 --> 00:32:57,685
Why'd you ignore my messages?

528
00:32:57,768 --> 00:33:00,229
Why're you here?
Can't you see I'm working?

529
00:33:00,312 --> 00:33:02,523
I'll wait 'til you're done.

530
00:33:02,606 --> 00:33:04,400
Don't. You're bothering me.

531
00:33:05,192 --> 00:33:07,945
I'll stop by every day.
Will you listen to me then?

532
00:33:11,156 --> 00:33:14,618
Anyway, I'll see you after work.
Go wait elsewhere.

533
00:33:17,871 --> 00:33:20,541
How about Traditional Café Paris
by Mitaka station?

534
00:33:20,624 --> 00:33:22,084
Why Mitaka?

535
00:33:22,167 --> 00:33:25,087
Why not? I'll head over at five,
when I get off.

536
00:33:25,170 --> 00:33:27,548
-Promise?
-Promise.

537
00:33:29,007 --> 00:33:32,928
TRADITIONAL CAFÉ PARIS

538
00:33:33,011 --> 00:33:35,681
One egg sandwich and tea, please.

539
00:33:36,890 --> 00:33:39,977
A spaghetti Napolitan for me.

540
00:33:40,060 --> 00:33:41,520
Understood.

541
00:33:41,603 --> 00:33:43,439
One egg sandwich and one Napolitan.

542
00:33:43,522 --> 00:33:44,690
Yes.

543
00:33:55,033 --> 00:33:58,954
Chloe? What's with the outfit?

544
00:34:00,080 --> 00:34:02,249
I must see this mission through.

545
00:34:06,462 --> 00:34:08,213
Once Mimasaka and Tsukumo arrive,

546
00:34:08,297 --> 00:34:13,343
I'll stage a photo with them
"accidentally" in the background.

547
00:34:13,427 --> 00:34:15,471
I'll then post it on Paris's
social media account.

548
00:34:16,138 --> 00:34:18,098
No need to nudge Baba,
she'll come on her own.

549
00:34:18,182 --> 00:34:19,183
POST

550
00:34:19,266 --> 00:34:22,436
She's a café lover who already
follows Paris's account.

551
00:34:22,519 --> 00:34:23,896
TRADITIONAL CAFÉ PARIS

552
00:34:28,525 --> 00:34:31,236
Thank you for waiting. Enjoy.

553
00:34:31,862 --> 00:34:33,822
Let me snap some photos.

554
00:34:34,323 --> 00:34:36,450
Phew, your Napolitan's steamy.
Looks delish.

555
00:34:36,533 --> 00:34:38,327
I'll post a pic on my account.

556
00:34:38,410 --> 00:34:39,787
Don't copy me.

557
00:34:39,870 --> 00:34:42,915
You're the one trying to get likes
using my food.

558
00:34:42,998 --> 00:34:45,417
Mimasaka, the egg sandwich lover,

559
00:34:45,501 --> 00:34:47,419
has a habit of uploading
pictures of egg sandwiches

560
00:34:47,503 --> 00:34:50,964
along with hashtags
and information about the café.

561
00:34:51,048 --> 00:34:53,300
I POST INFO ON CAFÉS
WITH TASTY EGG SANDWICHES!

562
00:34:53,383 --> 00:34:55,844
Sorita, the hot model,
follows Mimasaka's account.

563
00:34:55,928 --> 00:34:58,555
He should catch on that she's here.

564
00:35:01,308 --> 00:35:02,893
It's out of this world!

565
00:35:05,479 --> 00:35:07,439
You sure eat like you love food.

566
00:35:07,940 --> 00:35:10,192
You want to say that's why I'm fat, huh?

567
00:35:10,275 --> 00:35:13,237
No. Just thought I like
how happy you look.

568
00:35:15,197 --> 00:35:17,699
You can't sweet-talk me
into getting back with you.

569
00:35:19,368 --> 00:35:21,995
Isn't there a hot model who's into you?

570
00:35:22,704 --> 00:35:26,250
You already know
he's not a good match for you, right?

571
00:35:26,333 --> 00:35:29,545
-None of your business.
-Well, you should follow your gut.

572
00:35:29,628 --> 00:35:31,797
I've dated a pretty girl before,

573
00:35:31,880 --> 00:35:36,093
but everyone looks at you like you've got
no right to be with an attractive person.

574
00:35:36,176 --> 00:35:40,514
Before long, you start to take
everything they say the wrong way.

575
00:35:43,016 --> 00:35:45,269
Life was simple
when I was with you, Haruka.

576
00:35:45,352 --> 00:35:47,354
Didn't you feel the same?

577
00:35:48,230 --> 00:35:50,274
You treated me carelessly toward the end.

578
00:35:50,357 --> 00:35:52,442
I'm really sorry.

579
00:35:52,526 --> 00:35:54,319
I was immature.

580
00:35:55,362 --> 00:36:00,158
Recently, all I can think about
is the good times we shared.

581
00:36:01,159 --> 00:36:06,248
Remember the accessory-making workshop
we went to together?

582
00:36:06,331 --> 00:36:09,293
I made weird earrings,
and you couldn't stop laughing.

583
00:36:09,960 --> 00:36:13,088
What was it? What did I make again?

584
00:36:15,549 --> 00:36:18,176
Right. Burnt toast!

585
00:36:18,260 --> 00:36:21,847
I loved how you wore them all the time.
Did you throw them away?

586
00:36:29,062 --> 00:36:31,481
Look how strong he comes on.

587
00:36:31,565 --> 00:36:33,901
So that's how abuse starts.

588
00:36:34,401 --> 00:36:36,236
This place is empty.

589
00:36:36,320 --> 00:36:37,613
I didn't mean to get it…

590
00:36:37,696 --> 00:36:40,407
Welcome in. For one?

591
00:36:41,825 --> 00:36:44,119
You never took interest in things I wear.

592
00:36:44,202 --> 00:36:46,288
-Say what?
-Interest.

593
00:36:51,168 --> 00:36:52,169
Tsukumo.

594
00:36:53,629 --> 00:36:54,880
Ritsuko? Why're you here?

595
00:36:56,006 --> 00:36:57,883
-Hey…
-You know her, Ken?

596
00:36:57,966 --> 00:36:59,092
I'm his girlfriend.

597
00:37:02,679 --> 00:37:04,681
How'd you know I'd be here?

598
00:37:06,224 --> 00:37:09,061
That's you in the background, right?

599
00:37:10,270 --> 00:37:12,230
That's how you found out where I am?

600
00:37:12,856 --> 00:37:14,024
You creep me out.

601
00:37:15,317 --> 00:37:17,235
I want a Napolitan too.

602
00:37:18,111 --> 00:37:19,780
-Excuse me.
-Yes?

603
00:37:25,410 --> 00:37:26,745
One Napolitan, please.

604
00:37:26,828 --> 00:37:28,288
Just a moment, Miss.

605
00:37:33,710 --> 00:37:34,836
Welcome in.

606
00:37:34,920 --> 00:37:36,380
For one?

607
00:37:36,922 --> 00:37:39,049
-Everyone's here.
-Sit wherever you'd like.

608
00:37:43,637 --> 00:37:47,015
Ritsuko, don't stalk me anymore.

609
00:37:47,099 --> 00:37:48,475
It really gets on my nerves.

610
00:37:48,558 --> 00:37:51,561
Why are you going behind my back
to meet up with your ex?

611
00:37:52,396 --> 00:37:55,649
You used to date him, right?

612
00:37:58,026 --> 00:37:59,027
Yes.

613
00:37:59,111 --> 00:38:01,113
I can meet with whomever I want.

614
00:38:01,196 --> 00:38:03,407
See how controlling you are?

615
00:38:03,490 --> 00:38:06,076
This is why no one else but me
would ever date you, you get that?

616
00:38:06,159 --> 00:38:07,369
Hey, Ken.

617
00:38:08,245 --> 00:38:11,623
I might have dated him,

618
00:38:11,707 --> 00:38:13,709
but I have no intention
of getting back with him.

619
00:38:13,792 --> 00:38:15,252
You can relax.

620
00:38:15,335 --> 00:38:17,629
And I don't plan on ever
talking to him again.

621
00:38:17,713 --> 00:38:19,172
Wait, what?

622
00:38:20,215 --> 00:38:21,341
Seriously?

623
00:38:25,846 --> 00:38:30,392
Look what you've done.
You're ruining my friendships.

624
00:38:30,475 --> 00:38:31,977
How will you make up for it?

625
00:38:33,145 --> 00:38:36,606
Do you realize what you've done?
Why do you do this to me?

626
00:38:36,690 --> 00:38:38,275
That's too far.

627
00:38:38,358 --> 00:38:40,902
It's for her own good.
Otherwise, she'd never stop.

628
00:38:40,986 --> 00:38:43,488
She might be pretty, but she's immature.

629
00:38:43,572 --> 00:38:44,865
Hey, you--

630
00:38:44,948 --> 00:38:47,284
I'm saying this for your own good.

631
00:38:47,367 --> 00:38:50,537
If you stalk me again,
I'm cutting ties with you.

632
00:38:50,620 --> 00:38:53,498
Then you'll be left all alone.

633
00:38:53,582 --> 00:38:54,916
You understand that?

634
00:38:58,211 --> 00:39:01,840
I know I've got no right to say this,

635
00:39:01,923 --> 00:39:03,800
but why are you dating scum like him?

636
00:39:04,384 --> 00:39:07,804
He's hitting on his ex while he's dating
you. Don't you see how shitty that is?

637
00:39:08,972 --> 00:39:13,393
I bet you're saying that to break us up.
Do you want to get back with him?

638
00:39:14,770 --> 00:39:17,981
Come on. He's not worth fighting over.

639
00:39:18,065 --> 00:39:19,566
Wow, you're so rude.

640
00:39:19,649 --> 00:39:22,444
Everything you've said so far is abusive.

641
00:39:22,527 --> 00:39:25,572
You're tearing down her confidence
so you can feel superior to her.

642
00:39:25,655 --> 00:39:27,657
Sorry to keep you waiting. Your Napoli--

643
00:39:28,742 --> 00:39:30,077
I know.

644
00:39:31,119 --> 00:39:33,955
You're jealous because she's pretty.

645
00:39:34,998 --> 00:39:36,249
Say what?

646
00:39:36,333 --> 00:39:40,754
Are you satisfied that an ugly girl
like you got to tell off a beautiful girl?

647
00:39:40,837 --> 00:39:42,130
I know you are.

648
00:39:43,298 --> 00:39:45,217
You're the worst.

649
00:39:45,801 --> 00:39:47,511
-Here's the Napolitan--
-Hey!

650
00:39:48,595 --> 00:39:50,764
Will you stop criticizing Mimasaka?

651
00:39:50,847 --> 00:39:52,474
You're the one fixated on appearance.

652
00:39:53,350 --> 00:39:54,476
Masahiko?

653
00:39:54,559 --> 00:39:57,479
I heard Mimasaka got
in a spat with a customer.

654
00:39:57,562 --> 00:40:00,440
I got worried and came looking for you.
The café owner told me everything.

655
00:40:00,524 --> 00:40:03,068
I used your hashtags
as a clue to come here.

656
00:40:03,151 --> 00:40:06,363
You creep.
You're a stalker just like Ritsuko.

657
00:40:07,114 --> 00:40:09,866
You're the one who tracked down
her workplace and barged in uninvited.

658
00:40:09,950 --> 00:40:11,451
Here's your Napolitan.

659
00:40:11,535 --> 00:40:13,036
Let's go, Mimasaka.

660
00:40:13,120 --> 00:40:17,290
He's projecting his own insecurities about
his appearance on you and his girlfriend.

661
00:40:19,209 --> 00:40:22,921
Are you unaware of how condescending
you sound right now?

662
00:40:23,004 --> 00:40:25,423
Just what I'd expect
from someone as attractive as you.

663
00:40:27,509 --> 00:40:30,846
Listen. I don't think
I'm better looking than anyone.

664
00:40:32,973 --> 00:40:34,850
Don't worry about appearances.

665
00:40:35,600 --> 00:40:37,310
I chose you. Won't you trust me?

666
00:40:45,527 --> 00:40:47,154
It doesn't sit right with me.

667
00:40:48,155 --> 00:40:50,740
Ken tells me not to step out of line
because I'm ugly.

668
00:40:50,824 --> 00:40:53,535
Masahiko says he doesn't care if I'm ugly.

669
00:40:54,619 --> 00:40:57,080
Either way, you're both
fixated on appearances.

670
00:40:57,831 --> 00:41:00,208
To me, both of you sound condescending.

671
00:41:01,459 --> 00:41:03,628
If that's how I came across,
then I apologize.

672
00:41:04,171 --> 00:41:07,424
Besides, I never
used the word "ugly." I just--

673
00:41:07,507 --> 00:41:11,011
You said popular girls are intimidating.

674
00:41:11,094 --> 00:41:13,096
That's why you prefer me.

675
00:41:13,180 --> 00:41:17,642
Because I'm not the popular type,
meaning, you like unattractive girls.

676
00:41:19,060 --> 00:41:20,687
You'd rather date a girl
who's a downgrade.

677
00:41:20,770 --> 00:41:22,981
It sure is more comfortable that way.

678
00:41:23,064 --> 00:41:24,482
That's not what I meant.

679
00:41:25,066 --> 00:41:28,945
People who think they are beautiful
tend to be haughty.

680
00:41:29,029 --> 00:41:30,906
They don't even realize
they're looking down on others.

681
00:41:31,823 --> 00:41:33,950
Aren't you describing yourself?

682
00:41:34,576 --> 00:41:36,578
That was astute, Ritsuko.

683
00:41:36,661 --> 00:41:39,080
What? Who are you again?

684
00:41:39,664 --> 00:41:43,585
At least, I've never made fun
of the people around me.

685
00:41:43,668 --> 00:41:46,046
I know I'm no one special.

686
00:41:46,880 --> 00:41:48,924
Here's a thought.

687
00:41:49,007 --> 00:41:52,719
Maybe you're used to being degraded
by the people in your life.

688
00:41:53,428 --> 00:41:56,056
Exactly. And sorry to say this,

689
00:41:56,139 --> 00:41:58,934
but objectively speaking,
he treats you like trash.

690
00:41:59,601 --> 00:42:03,355
Butt out of our business.
She's the one who needs me.

691
00:42:03,438 --> 00:42:06,816
Seriously, why does it have to be him?

692
00:42:06,900 --> 00:42:09,986
She's right. You're bound to find
a better man in a heartbeat.

693
00:42:13,156 --> 00:42:16,159
You hear that? What're you going to do?

694
00:42:16,243 --> 00:42:17,494
We all have different reasons,

695
00:42:17,577 --> 00:42:21,790
but all three of us think
you'd be better off without me.

696
00:42:21,873 --> 00:42:25,585
Why don't you break up with me
and doll up like this model?

697
00:42:26,086 --> 00:42:30,340
Like he said,
you'll get swarmed by trashy men.

698
00:42:30,423 --> 00:42:32,175
You're really pretty, after all.

699
00:42:32,259 --> 00:42:35,303
You're the worst.
You're the one who's trash.

700
00:42:35,387 --> 00:42:36,554
He got that right.

701
00:42:43,603 --> 00:42:46,106
There you go. Silent treatment again?

702
00:42:47,315 --> 00:42:49,067
Want me to decide for you?

703
00:42:52,195 --> 00:42:53,321
I won't break up.

704
00:42:55,532 --> 00:42:57,117
I'm never breaking up with you.

705
00:42:58,410 --> 00:43:00,287
What? Why?

706
00:43:00,996 --> 00:43:03,039
He's my first boyfriend,

707
00:43:03,123 --> 00:43:05,125
and he took my virginity.

708
00:43:05,208 --> 00:43:08,169
I even enrolled in a university
below my grades to be with him.

709
00:43:09,587 --> 00:43:12,173
If I break up with him now,
then my life from 17 to 19,

710
00:43:12,257 --> 00:43:15,760
the most wonderful time of youth,
would be wasted.

711
00:43:15,844 --> 00:43:18,596
Come on. That's like losing out on a bet

712
00:43:18,680 --> 00:43:22,183
and digging a deeper hole
to recover from it.

713
00:43:22,684 --> 00:43:25,478
The faster you break up with
this shitty guy, the better off you'll be.

714
00:43:25,562 --> 00:43:30,150
What's wrong with you,
calling me a losing bet and shit?

715
00:43:30,859 --> 00:43:34,946
He's not shit.
I didn't waste my life on a shitty guy.

716
00:43:35,030 --> 00:43:39,200
I love him, regardless
of his personality and appearance.

717
00:43:39,784 --> 00:43:42,662
What's wrong with that?
Did I hurt someone?

718
00:43:42,746 --> 00:43:47,000
He's got the worst personality around,
and his features are average at best.

719
00:43:47,083 --> 00:43:49,044
So what?

720
00:43:49,127 --> 00:43:51,087
For me, there's no one else but him,

721
00:43:51,171 --> 00:43:53,298
and for him, there's no one else but me.

722
00:43:53,840 --> 00:43:56,760
I'm the only one he can treat like this.

723
00:43:58,094 --> 00:44:00,930
We're a good match. We suit each other.

724
00:44:01,556 --> 00:44:03,016
Isn't that enough?

725
00:44:10,607 --> 00:44:13,026
She really didn't hold back.

726
00:44:13,902 --> 00:44:15,945
You good?

727
00:44:20,325 --> 00:44:22,494
That was a bit much.

728
00:44:22,577 --> 00:44:23,912
What?

729
00:44:23,995 --> 00:44:26,581
Me? It's my fault?

730
00:44:27,374 --> 00:44:29,709
I professed my love for him.

731
00:44:31,669 --> 00:44:33,213
Sorry about the Napolitan.

732
00:44:33,838 --> 00:44:36,174
I'm sure the pasta's soggy
and your arm is tired.

733
00:44:37,092 --> 00:44:38,176
Right.

734
00:44:41,429 --> 00:44:42,639
Sorry for the wait.

735
00:44:43,973 --> 00:44:45,183
Here's your Napolitan.

736
00:44:51,481 --> 00:44:52,690
Digging in.

737
00:45:18,716 --> 00:45:20,051
In this world,

738
00:45:21,010 --> 00:45:23,638
there are as many types of hell
as there are people.

739
00:45:26,141 --> 00:45:29,185
I thought you were going
to solve everyone's problems

740
00:45:29,269 --> 00:45:33,189
like they do in cartoons and dramas.

741
00:45:34,274 --> 00:45:35,859
I had nothing to say.

742
00:45:36,609 --> 00:45:39,863
Thinking I could swoop in
and save the day…

743
00:45:40,447 --> 00:45:42,031
Really, I was misguided.

744
00:45:48,246 --> 00:45:50,457
Thanks for waiting.

745
00:45:51,916 --> 00:45:52,917
Nice.

746
00:45:57,797 --> 00:45:59,966
-Here you go.
-Thank you.

747
00:46:03,011 --> 00:46:04,012
Enjoy.

748
00:46:04,095 --> 00:46:05,305
Thank you.

749
00:46:08,224 --> 00:46:11,436
This week, I made
a grown-up karinto parfait.

750
00:46:14,147 --> 00:46:16,357
The bottom layer is
hoji tea and lemon jelly.

751
00:46:16,441 --> 00:46:19,777
It's topped with crushed
brown-sugar karinto and yogurt cream,

752
00:46:19,861 --> 00:46:21,529
as well as blueberries and raspberries.

753
00:46:21,613 --> 00:46:23,281
At the center is
bamboo charcoal ice cream.

754
00:46:23,364 --> 00:46:26,784
At the top are
salt-and-black-pepper skinny karinto

755
00:46:26,868 --> 00:46:28,286
and a bamboo charcoal tuile.

756
00:46:29,162 --> 00:46:31,456
A Japanese parfait for grown-ups indeed.

757
00:46:31,539 --> 00:46:33,708
-Time to dig in.
-Thank you for the parfait.

758
00:46:42,926 --> 00:46:46,054
The black pepper and salt
bring out the karinto's sweet flavor.

759
00:46:46,137 --> 00:46:47,514
They're in perfect harmony.

760
00:46:49,057 --> 00:46:52,185
A yummy parfait is a great way to forget
the hell we witnessed.

761
00:46:54,479 --> 00:47:00,151
My own lack of insight, shortcomings,
the negative emotions of others…

762
00:47:04,322 --> 00:47:06,616
This is a ritual to purge them all.

763
00:47:12,539 --> 00:47:16,793
To tell you the truth,
karinto parfait is how I got started.

764
00:47:16,876 --> 00:47:18,002
What?

765
00:47:18,503 --> 00:47:21,422
When I was in elementary school,
someone stole my recorder.

766
00:47:21,506 --> 00:47:23,299
Don't worry, we found the thief.

767
00:47:24,342 --> 00:47:29,347
My teacher said, "She stole it because
she likes you. Can't you let it go?"

768
00:47:29,430 --> 00:47:30,765
No way.

769
00:47:31,266 --> 00:47:34,769
It didn't sit right with me.
Why do I have to be the bigger person?

770
00:47:35,436 --> 00:47:38,147
I went home feeling depressed.

771
00:47:38,231 --> 00:47:41,192
My parents gave me karinto to cheer me up.

772
00:47:41,776 --> 00:47:44,320
I don't dislike karinto per se,

773
00:47:45,154 --> 00:47:47,615
but back then, I was furious
it had to be karinto.

774
00:47:48,324 --> 00:47:50,451
It was the last straw,
and I started bawling.

775
00:47:52,829 --> 00:47:55,039
You must have wanted pudding

776
00:47:55,123 --> 00:47:57,917
or another soft and sweet treat
after such a rough day.

777
00:48:01,296 --> 00:48:04,882
But then, I found a tub of yogurt
in the fridge,

778
00:48:04,966 --> 00:48:06,926
so I made a karinto yogurt parfait.

779
00:48:07,010 --> 00:48:09,679
All I did was pour yogurt
over some karinto.

780
00:48:11,347 --> 00:48:13,266
I bet it felt fancy.

781
00:48:16,269 --> 00:48:20,064
I felt a bit better after I finished it.

782
00:48:22,233 --> 00:48:23,401
I see.

783
00:48:23,985 --> 00:48:28,865
Little Simon had to pull himself up by his
bootstraps and find his own happiness.

784
00:48:32,327 --> 00:48:37,790
We all dream that someone can
come into our lives and make us happy.

785
00:48:37,874 --> 00:48:39,792
Expect it, even.

786
00:48:39,876 --> 00:48:43,212
But life is full of regrets
and what-could-have-beens.

787
00:48:44,922 --> 00:48:47,091
In the end, you're
the only person in the world

788
00:48:47,175 --> 00:48:49,260
who can provide the happiness you seek.

789
00:48:50,094 --> 00:48:52,263
Life is about coming to that realization.

790
00:48:52,347 --> 00:48:55,141
Maybe that's the thing

791
00:48:55,683 --> 00:48:57,477
that separates us from them.

792
00:48:59,729 --> 00:49:00,855
But you know…

793
00:49:04,317 --> 00:49:07,070
it takes privilege to realize that.

794
00:49:08,237 --> 00:49:09,405
Come again?

795
00:49:09,989 --> 00:49:13,451
We have to be somewhat comfortable
before we can come to that realization.

796
00:49:14,786 --> 00:49:17,455
Money, beauty, talent…

797
00:49:18,831 --> 00:49:21,459
I hope we can live in a world
where people who lack all these things

798
00:49:21,542 --> 00:49:25,129
can still enjoy
delicious parfaits like this.

799
00:49:30,176 --> 00:49:33,721
You have to get on your feet first.

800
00:49:34,514 --> 00:49:35,765
I know.

801
00:49:36,265 --> 00:49:40,561
I hope you can afford Simon's parfait
with your own money soon.

802
00:49:40,645 --> 00:49:41,896
Yes.

803
00:49:42,605 --> 00:49:46,150
I will work hard so that I can
open my own parfait shop someday.

804
00:49:46,234 --> 00:49:47,402
You can bet on it.

805
00:49:49,362 --> 00:49:50,488
I'll pour you some tea.

806
00:49:50,571 --> 00:49:51,906
Thank you.

807
00:49:54,450 --> 00:49:56,869
Yogurt and brown sugar karinto…

808
00:50:00,707 --> 00:50:02,458
It's a match made in heaven.
